The paper discusses the use of machine learning and deep neural nets to learn fair representations, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of bias and discrimination in high-stakes applications, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses information theory to provide theoretical results, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CY).
